Definition: [ἀδήλως] adverb from {{g82}}; uncertainly
[ἀδημονέω] from a derivative of ἀδέω (to be sated to loathing); to be in distress (of mind)
[ᾅδης] from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g1492}}; properly, unseen, i.e. "Hades" or the place (state) of departed souls
[ἀδιάκριτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g1252}}; properly, undistinguished, i.e. (actively) impartial
[ἀδελφός] from {{g1}} (as a connective particle) and δελφύς (the womb); a brother (literally or figuratively) near or remote (much like {{g1}})
[ἀδελφότης] from {{g80}}; brotherhood (properly, the feeling of brotherliness), i.e. the (Christian) fraternity
[ἄδηλος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1212}}; hidden, figuratively, indistinct
[ἀδηλότης] from {{g82}}; uncertainty
[ἀδιάλειπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of {{g1223}} and {{g3007}}; unintermitted, i.e. permanent
[ἀδιαλείπτως] adverb from {{g88}}; uninterruptedly, i.e. without omission (on an appropriate occasion)
[Ἀβιά] of Hebrew origin ({{h29}}); Abijah, the name of two Israelites
[Ἄβελ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1893}}); Abel, the son of Adam
[Ἀββᾶ] of Chaldee origin ({{h2}}); father as a vocative
[ἀβαρής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g922}}; weightless, i.e. (figuratively) not burdensome
[Ἀβαδδών] of Hebrew origin ({{h11}}); a destroying angel
[Ἀαρών] of Hebrew origin ({{h175}}); Aaron, the brother of Moses

[Α] of Hebrew origin; the first letter of the alphabet; figuratively, only (from its use as a numeral) the first:  Often used (usually ἄν, before a vowel) also in composition (as a contraction from {{g427}}) in the sense of privation; so, in many words, beginning with this letter; occasionally in the sense of union (as a contraction of {{g260}}).
[Ἀβιληνή] of foreign origin (compare {{h58}}); Abilene, a region of Syria
[Ἀβιαθάρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h54}}); Abiathar, an Israelite
[ἀγγελία] from {{g32}}; an announcement, i.e. (by implication) precept
[ἀγγεῖον] from ἄγγος (a pail, perhaps as bent; compare the base of {{g43}}); a receptacle
[ἄγε] imperative of {{g71}}; properly, lead, i.e. come on
[ἄγγελος] from ἀγγέλλω (probably derived from {{g71}}; compare {{g34}}) (to bring tidings); a messenger; especially an "angel"; by implication, a pastor
[ἀγενεαλόγητος] from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g1075}}; unregistered as to birth
[ἀγέλη] from {{g71}} (compare {{g32}}); a drove
[ἁγιάζω] from {{g40}}; to make holy, i.e. (ceremonially) purify or consecrate; (mentally) to venerate
[ἀγενής] from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g1085}}; properly, without kin, i.e. (of unknown descent, and by implication) ignoble
[ἅγιον] neuter of {{g40}}; a sacred thing (i.e. spot)
[ἁγιασμός] from {{g37}}; properly, purification, i.e. (the state) purity; concretely (by Hebraism) a purifier
[ἀγάπη] from {{g25}}; love, i.e. affection or benevolence; specially (plural) a love-feast
[ἀγαπητός] from {{g25}}; beloved
[ἀγανάκτησις] from {{g23}}; indignation
[ἀγαπάω] perhaps from ἄγαν (much) (or compare {{h5689}}); to love (in a social or moral sense) Compare {{g5368}}.
[ἄγαμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1062}}; unmarried
[ἀγανακτέω] from ἄγαν (much) and ἄχθος (grief; akin to the base of {{g43}}); to be greatly afflicted, i.e. (figuratively) indignant
[ἀγαλλίασις] from {{g21}}; exultation; specially, welcome
[ἀγαλλιάω] from agan (much) and {{g242}}; properly, to jump for joy, i.e. exult
[Ἄγαρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1904}}); Hagar, the concubine of Abraham
[ἀγγαρεύω] of foreign origin (compare {{h104}}); properly, to be a courier, i.e. (by implication) to press into public service
[ἁδρότης] from ἁδρός (stout); plumpness, i.e. (figuratively) liberality
[ἁγνός] from the same as {{g40}}; properly, clean, i.e. (figuratively) innocent, modest, perfect
[ἄγνοια] from {{g50}}; ignorance (properly, the quality)
[ἀγνόημα] from {{g50}}; a thing ignored, i.e. shortcoming
[ἀγνοέω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3539}}; not to know (through lack of information or intelligence); by implication, to ignore (through disinclination)
[ἄγνωστος] from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g1110}}; unknown
[ἀγνωσία] from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g1108}}; ignorance (properly, the state)
[ἁγνῶς] adverb from {{g53}}; purely, i.e. honestly
[ἁγνότης] from {{g53}}; cleanness (the state), i.e. (figuratively) blamelessness
[ἀγοράζω] from {{g58}}; properly, to go to market, i.e. (by implication) to purchase; specially, to redeem
[ἀγορά] from ἀγείρω (to gather; probably akin to {{g1453}}); properly, the town-square (as a place of public resort); by implication, a market or thoroughfare
[ἅγιος] from ἅγος (an awful thing) (compare {{g53}}, {{g2282}}); sacred (physically, pure, morally blameless or religious, ceremonially, consecrated)
[ἁγιότης] from {{g40}}; sanctity (i.e. properly, the state)
[ἁγιωσύνη] from {{g40}}; sacredness (i.e. properly, the quality)
[ἀγκάλη] from ἄγκος (a bend, "ache"); an arm (as curved)
[ἄγκιστρον] from the same as {{g43}}; a hook (as bent)
[ἄγκυρα] from the same as {{g43}}; an "anchor" (as crooked)
[ἄγναφος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the same as {{g1102}}; properly, unfulled, i.e. (by implication) new (cloth)
[ἁγνεία] from {{g53}}; cleanliness (the quality), i.e. (specially) chastity
[ἁγνίζω] from {{g53}}; to make clean, i.e. (figuratively) sanctify (ceremonially or morally)
[ἁγνισμός] from {{g48}}; a cleansing (the act), i.e. (ceremonially) lustration
[ἀγωνίζομαι] from {{g73}}; to struggle, literally (to compete for a prize), figuratively (to contend with an adversary), or genitive case (to endeavor to accomplish something)
[ἀγωνία] from {{g73}}; a struggle (properly, the state), i.e. (figuratively) anguish
[ἀδάπανος] from {{g1}} (as negative particle); and {{g1160}}; costless, i.e. gratuitous
[Ἀδάμ] of Hebrew origin ({{h121}}); Adam, the first man; typically (of Jesus) man (as his representative)
[ἄγω] a primary verb; properly, to lead; by implication, to bring, drive, (reflexively) go, (specially) pass (time), or (figuratively) induce
[ἀγρυπνία] from {{g69}}; sleeplessness, i.e. a keeping awake
[ἀγών] from {{g71}}; properly, a place of assembly (as if led), i.e. (by implication) a contest (held there); figuratively, an effort or anxiety
[ἀγωγή] reduplicated from {{g71}}; a bringing up, i.e. mode of living
[ἀδελφή] feminine of {{g80}}; a sister (naturally or ecclesiastically)
[Ἀδδί] probably of Hebrew origin (compare {{h5716}}); Addi, an Israelite
[ἀγρός] from {{g71}}; a field (as a drive for cattle); genitive case, the country; specially, a farm, i.e. hamlet
[ἀγρυπνέω] ultimately from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g5258}}; to be sleepless, i.e. keep awake
[ἀγράμματος] from {{g1}} (as negative particle) and {{g1121}}; unlettered, i.e. illiterate
[ἀγραυλέω] from {{g68}} and {{g832}} (in the sense of {{g833}}); to camp out
[ἀγοραῖος] from {{g58}}; relating to the market-place, i.e. forensic (times); by implication, vulgar
[ἄγρα] from {{g71}}; (abstractly) a catching (of fish); also (concretely) a haul (of fish)
[ἄγριος] from {{g68}}; wild (as pertaining to the country), literally (natural) or figuratively (fierce)
[Ἀγρίππας] apparently from {{g66}} and {{g2462}}; wild-horse tamer; Agrippas, one of the Herods
[ἀγρεύω] from {{g61}}; to hunt, i.e. (figuratively) to entrap
[ἀγριέλαιος] from {{g66}} and {{g1636}}; an oleaster
[ἄδολος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle); and {{g1388}}; undeceitful, i.e. (figuratively) unadulterated
[ἀδόκιμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1384}}; unapproved, i.e. rejected; by implication, worthless (literally or morally)
[ἀδίκως] adverb from {{g94}}; unjustly
[ἄδικος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1349}}; unjust; by extension wicked; by implication, treacherous; specially, heathen
[ἀδικία] from {{g94}}; (legal) injustice (properly, the quality, by implication, the act); morally, wrongfulness (of character, life or act)
[ἀδίκημα] from {{g91}}; a wrong done
[ἀδικέω] from {{g94}}; to be unjust, i.e. (actively) do wrong (morally, socially or physically)
[ἀδιαφθορία] from a derivative of a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g1311}}; incorruptibleness, i.e. (figuratively) purity (of doctrine)
[Ἀδρίας] from Ἀδρία (a place near its shore); the Adriatic sea (including the Ionian)
[Ἀδραμυττηνός] from Ἀδραμύττειον (a place in Asia Minor); Adramyttene or belonging to Adramyttium
[ἀγαθωσύνη] from {{g18}}; goodness, i.e. virtue or beneficence
[ἀγαθός] a primary word; "good" (in any sense, often as noun) Compare {{g2570}}.
[ἀγαθοποιός] from {{g18}} and {{g4160}}; a well-doer, i.e. virtuous
[ἀγαθοποιΐα] from {{g17}}; well-doing, i.e. virtue
[ἀγαθοποιέω] from {{g17}}; to be a well-doer (as a favor or a duty)
[ἀγαθοεργέω] from {{g18}} and {{g2041}}; to work good
[Ἄγαβος] of Hebrew origin (compare {{h2285}}); Agabus, an Israelite
[ἄβυσσος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a variation of {{g1037}}; depthless, i.e. (specially) (infernal) "abyss"
[Ἀβραάμ] of Hebrew origin ({{h85}}); Abraham, the Hebrew patriarch (In Acts 7:16 the text should probably read Jacob.)
[Ἀβιούδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h31}}); Abihud, an Israelite
